Although Kenya is a multi-cultural and multi-religion society, tolerance and respect are a two-way street. The noise from the call to prayer from mosques in the CBD and near residential areas is too much. Mosque leaders should respect the fact that not all Kenyans are Muslims and realise that it is unnecessary to blast the call to prayer on loudspeaker. In the CBD, this is a disturbance to office workers who may have reported to work a few hours earlier for one reason or another. In the modern day, Islam leaders could send out mobile messages to call followers.  Nairobi